<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900723-0064</DOCNO><DOCID>900723-0064.</DOCID><HL>   Technology:   Advanced Micro Posts Loss</HL><DATE>07/23/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A7</SO><CO>   AMD</CO><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   SUNNYVALE, Calif. -- Advanced Micro Devices Inc.'s stockskidded Friday on a report that the chip maker posted a netloss of $5.9 million, or 10 cents a share, for its secondquarter ended July 1.   Advanced Micro was expected to break even or turn a smallprofit of as much as five cents a share. The company's losswould have been even larger had the quarter not included a$6.1 million gain from the sale of its stake in another chipmaker. In New York Stock Exchange composite trading Friday,Advanced Micro's shares closed at $7.25, down $1.75.</LP><TEXT>   Analysts blamed the poor results on a shortfall of roughly$17 million in revenue, which overall declined 2.6% to $267.7million from $274.9 million. The decline was caused by a 29%drop in the price of the company's 286 microprocessor. A lackof availability of certain memory and logic chips also hurtsales.   In the year-earlier period, Advanced Micro earned $12.1million, or 12 cents a share.</TEXT></DOC>